      "lineNbr": 56,
      "author": {
        "id": 1118104
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-05-06T00:26:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "IIUC we use invocations.CurrentMaxShard() to get the number of shards in the data, rather than `const invocations.Shards` to make sure we are cleaning up all the data in the database rather than only up to the shardnumber hardcoded in the current binary.\n\nThis is patterned after the purger\u0027s code: https://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/main:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/resultdb/internal/services/purger/purger.go;drc\u003d158d2227f127bc98fc59725a88aa94513b5921b1;l\u003d63",
      "parentUuid": "02138374_5ffb866e",
      "revId": "1a7dd097e22be52a29edaa7f3396e2fe0bf66954",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "49de1a2d_95633e73",
        "filename": "resultdb/internal/services/deadlineenforcer/deadline_enforcer.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 56,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114919
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-05-06T09:13:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e IIUC we use invocations.CurrentMaxShard() to get the number of shards in the data, rather than `const invocations.Shards` to make sure we are cleaning up all the data in the database rather than only up to the shardnumber hardcoded in the current binary.\n\nYes, this is my understanding, too.\n\nHowever, my concern is that if MaxShards changes, it\u0027ll only be noticed by the purger or deadlineEnforce servers once the process is restarted. Ideally, this func is called by every ~cron iteration (the actual query is O(1) for spanner).\n\nIf we agree on the problem, then I propose to:\n1. Leave TODO in this CL, possibly also in purger package.\n2. Address TODO in a follow up CL by creating new func like this:\n  cron.AdjustableShards(ctx, func getShards(ctx) int, minInterval, oneShard)\nand using it from both purger and deadlineEnforcer.",
      "parentUuid": "ed91b8b3_23c790bb",
      "revId": "1a7dd097e22be52a29edaa7f3396e2fe0bf66954",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
